str:Codelist.com:Name: Time Format
str:Codelist.com:Description: This code list provides coded information (based on the ISO 8601 standard) indicating the type of time references used in the data. It was released in 2009. More information about this code list and SDMX code lists in general (e.g. list of generic codes for expressing general concepts like "Total", "Unknown", etc.; syntaxes for the creation of further codes; general guidelines for the creation of SDMX code lists) can be found at this address: https://sdmx.org/?page_id=4345.

str:Code.com:Name: CCYYMMDDhhmm
str:Code.com:Description: (Used in SDMX-EDI for series with freq. higher than daily) year/month/day/hours/minutes

str:Code.com:Name: CCYYMMDD
str:Code.com:Description: (Used in SDMX-EDI for daily and business series) year/month/day

str:Code.com:Name: CCYYWW
str:Code.com:Description: (Used in SDMX-EDI for weekly series) year/week

str:Code.com:Name: CCYYMM
str:Code.com:Description: (Used in SDMX-EDI for monthly series) year/month

str:Code.com:Name: CCYYQ
str:Code.com:Description: (Used in SDMX-EDI for quarterly series) year/quarter

str:Code.com:Name: CCYYS
str:Code.com:Description: (Used in SDMX-EDI for half yearly series) year/semester

str:Code.com:Name: CCYY
str:Code.com:Description: (Used in SDMX-EDI for annual series) year

str:Code.com:Name: CCYYMMDDhhmmCCYYMMDDhhmm
